# Default deny — only explicitly allowed files are tracked.
# Deny all files by default.
*

# Allow traversing directories (required for nested allow rules).
!*/

# Root files
!.gitignore
!LICENSE
!README.md
!GETTING-STARTED.md
!CHANGELOG.md
!server.json

# GitHub Actions
!.github/**

# Rust workspace
!rs/Cargo.toml
!rs/Cargo.lock

# ll-core crates (Tier 1: OSS infrastructure)
!rs/ll-core/**

# ll-open crates (Tier 2: OSS projection engine)
!rs/ll-open/**

# Workspace tools (compat-gen + future workspace-only binaries — not
# published as crates; live under rs/tools/ and are wired into the
# workspace via rs/Cargo.toml's `members = ["tools/*"]`).
!rs/tools/**

# Build infrastructure
!Taskfile.yml
!rs/pkgconfig/**
!entitlements.plist
# Repo-root tools/ — bash + allowlist artifacts driven from Taskfile (e.g.
# `task lint:blake3` reads `tools/blake3-allowlist.txt` and runs
# `tools/lint_blake3.sh`). Distinct from `rs/tools/` (workspace crates).
!tools/**

# Self-maintaining compat surface (bead ley-line-open-cbea02).
# Generated by `task compat:gen` from leyline-cli-lib::daemon::version
# constants; CI gate (`task compat:check`) fails on drift.
!compatibility.json

# Cross-language fixture trees consumed by tree-sitter parse + future
# integration tests. Small, parse-stable sources; tracked so smoke
# tests work after a fresh clone.
!tests/fixtures/**

# Image build — configs tracked, artifacts/keys local-only.
# Active path: `task image` uses krust + image.Dockerfile (see Taskfile.yml).
# apko/melange path was abandoned on Apple Silicon — see bead
# `ley-line-open-2b255c` for the post-mortem.
!image.Dockerfile

# Documentation
!docs/**

# Claude Code plugin wrappers — see wrappers/claude-code/ for the
# leyline-stale-sync plugin (cloister-acbf27). These are plugin
# sources tracked in the repo, not user-side .claude/ config.
!wrappers/**

# Rosary bead store (tracked across all repos in the workspace so beads
# survive machine moves / fresh clones / cross-agent handoff). Same
# pattern other repos in the workspace use (rosary/, mache/, signet/).
# Binary SQLite diff is acceptable for an N≈100 bead corpus.
!.beads/**
# SQLite WAL/shared-memory sidecars are transient — never commit.
.beads/*.db-wal
.beads/*.db-shm

# Go bindings module — clients/go/leyline-schema/ ships generated *.capnp.go
# files; the regen-diff CI gate (.github/workflows/leyline-schema-go.yml)
# requires them to be tracked, not gitignored.
!clients/**

# Re-deny build artifacts
**/target/
**/*.a
**/*.o
**/*.so
**/*.dylib
**/*.d

# CRUMB - personal memory (not tracked)
.crumb/
